TY  - JOUR
T1  - An Algorithm for a Nonlinear Discontinuous Knapsack Problem
AU  - Armstrong, R. D.
AU  - Cook, W. D.
AU  - Palacios-Gomez, F. E.
Y1  - 1979/09/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.25.9.884
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.25.9.884
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 884
EP  - 894
VL  - 25
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents a solution procedure for a class of discontinuous nonlinear knapsack problems. These problems have a single linear constraint and a restriction that each variable must be either zero or take on a value within a specified interval. The objective function is separable and each term is concave within the interval. Problems of this type arise in capital budgeting and a particular application in the scheduling of pavement maintenance is given. The branch-and-bound algorithm developed to solve the problem considers an approximation-relaxation at each step. Computational experience with the algorithm and a brief overview of applications of the model are given.
AB  - This paper presents a solution procedure for a class of discontinuous nonlinear knapsack problems. These problems have a single linear constraint and a restriction that each variable must be either zero or take on a value within a specified interval. The objective function is separable and each term is concave within the interval. Problems of this type arise in capital budgeting and a particular application in the scheduling of pavement maintenance is given. The branch-and-bound algorithm developed to solve the problem considers an approximation-relaxation at each step. Computational experience with the algorithm and a brief overview of applications of the model are given.
